criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. Age ≥ 65 years;

          2. Being scheduled to undergo an elective surgery (≥3 hours, general anesthesia) (e.g.,
             hip replacement or open reduction with internal fixation surgery for the repair of hip
             fractures);

          3. Being able to complete cognitive assessment and confusion assessment methods (CAM);

          4. Having normal cognitive function at the time of enrollment, e.g., Mini-Mental State
             Examination (MMSE) scores above 24;

          5. Chinese Mandarin as the native language;

          6. Willing to participate and being competent to provide informed consent.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Having preoperative delirium assessed by CAM;

          2. Having brain tumor, stroke, or mental disorders (e.g., depression or dementia);

          3. Having contraindications of cTBS (e.g., head trauma, history of epilepsy or metal
             implants in the head or heart);

          4. Participating in other clinical studies.
